Join Trane Technologies in this exciting opportunity.

A Foundational Company Rilla builds the world’s leading conversation intelligence software for offline commerce. By recording, analyzing, and indexing conversations, our platform supplies unparalleled alpha to the critical, physical businesses that constitute the backbone of our economy. Our purpose is to bring the technology of the 21st century’s most innovative companies to the rest of the economy. As a side effect of this mission, we’ve become one of the fastest growing companies in history. In numbers, that means 0→$40M in 3.5 years, growing 15% MoM, Net Revenue Retention above 170%, an NPS higher than the iPhone’s, and profitability. The Role Rilla engineers architect and ship features across the stack at lightning speed. On a daily basis, you will build end-to-end workflows, take them to production, and solve real world problems across an out-sized scale. As an early technical steward, you will raise the bar for code quality and decision‑making, setting patterns that cement a world‑class engineering culture as we scale. While the company 10×’s, your scope and ownership will grow just as fast—building the tools, mental models, and platforms that let both you and Rilla accelerate exponentially. Do you describe yourself as "obsessive"? Do you aspire to be a founder or a leader in applying AI to the physical world? We believe Rilla is the best place — with the best peers — to learn how. Technologies We Use Different languages and frameworks, including React, React Native, Typescript and Python Open-source technologies like Node.js, PostgreSQL, Turborepo, Lodash, and Zod Industry-standard build tooling, including GitHub Actions, Terraform, and Spacelift What We Value An infinite learner . Someone who is relentless in their curiosity. A customer obsessive . Someone who deeply care about delighting customers and solving real pains, not vanity metrics. A winning attitude . You thrive with extreme accountability, learning as a team, and both giving and receiving rapid feedback. Extreme empathy. Our customers are not tech companies. They live and work in the real world. Empathy is critical to arriving at correct solutions. Unafraid of failure. You take risks. You see failure as an opportunity to learn, grow, and be better the next time. In a weird way, you trick your brain into being excited when you fail, because it means you got a new opportunity to learn more. What We Require Strong coding skills with demonstrated proficiency in programming languages, such as Javascript, C++, Python, Rust, or similar languages. Strong engineering prowess, ideally developed at start-ups. Familiarity with storage and data processing systems, cloud infrastructure, and other technical tools. Strong written and verbal communication skills and ability to iterate quickly with teammates, incorporating feedback and holding a high bar for quality. Don’t Work Here Please don't join if you're not excited about: Building an AI product for an industry untouched by modern software Constantly talking to and visiting customers in the field Working ~70 hrs/week in person with some of the most ambitious people in NYC Attempting to build a generational company, and the intensity required to do so Our benefits aim to empower Rilla employees in removing roadblocks to achieving their life’s work. The list below details our available benefits and some of the perks that can be enjoyed as an employee of Rilla. Benefits Medical, dental, and vision insurance Breakfast, lunch, dinner, and supplementary food and drink — 6x a week Gym membership Commuter benefits Relocation assistance Take what you need paid time off, not accrual based $1,000 stipend for learning and personal growth $1,500 a month rent stipend Tech equipment

job_title: Intern – Business Transformation and Integration - Accounting Transformation and Integration Department
job_description: Click the link provided to see the complete job description.

Overview


Keysight is on the forefront of technology innovation, delivering breakthroughs and trusted insights in electronic design, simulation, prototyping, test, manufacturing, and optimization. Our ~15,000 employees create world-class solutions in communications, 5G, automotive, energy, quantum, aerospace, defense, and semiconductor markets for customers in over 100 countries. Learn more about what we do.

 

Our award-winning culture embraces a bold vision of where technology can take us and a passion for tackling challenging problems with industry-first solutions. We believe that when people feel a sense of belonging, they can be more creative, innovative, and thrive at all points in their careers.

 

Keysight is looking for a college intern who is passionate about Artificial Intelligence and excited to apply machine learning techniques to solve real-world problems. As a Machine Learning Engineer Intern, you will support our Data & Analytics and AI teams in developing, training, and evaluating ML models that enhance decision-making, automation, and customer experience across the company.

 

This role primarily focuses on learning and contributing to end-to-end ML workflows, including data preparation, feature engineering, model development, and performance evaluation. You will gain hands-on experience with modern ML frameworks and cloud-based AI platforms while working alongside experienced engineers and data scientists.


Responsibilities


  • Assist in building, training, and deploying machine learning models for predictive and analytical use cases.

  • Support data preparation tasks such as cleaning, feature engineering, and transformation for ML pipelines.

  • Conduct model evaluation, testing, and documentation to ensure performance and reliability.

  • Collaborate with data engineers on integrating ML models into scalable pipelines.

  • Explore opportunities to optimize model performance and improve inference efficiency.

  • Participate in research on emerging ML techniques, including deep learning and generative AI.

  • Additional learning opportunities in cloud ML/AI services as available.


Qualifications


 

  • Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with a foundation in mathematics and statistics.

  • Good communication skills and ability to collaborate in a team environment.

  • Familiarity with Python and ML libraries such as scikit-learn, TensorFlow, or PyTorch.

  • Understanding of supervised and unsupervised learning concepts; exposure to NLP or deep learning is a plus.

  • Knowledge of cloud platforms or MLOps practices is beneficial.

  • Team-oriented mindset with curiosity to learn and experiment with new AI techniques.

  • Currently enrolled in college with a major in Computer Science, Data Science, Artificial Intelligence, Information Systems, or related field. May consider business majors with an Information Systems or Data Analytics concentration.

Candidates who wish to be considered must be currently enrolled in a accredited college/university as of September 2026. Applicants who have graduated before September 2026 will not be considered unless they are starting a MS or PHD program after graduating.

 

Visa Sponsorship is not available for this position. Candidates who now or at any point in the future require sponsorship for post internship employment visa status (e.g., H-1B Visa status) may not be considered.

 
California Pay Range: $29.01-31.24 per hour
Based on experience, education and skills, most offers will be between the minimum and the midpoint of the Salary Range listed above.
Note: For other locations, pay ranges will vary by region.

Division

OmniSource

Overview

What Makes This Internship Different?

This Environmental Engineering Internship differs from typical programs because it is embedded in an active manufacturing environment where work informs real operational and sustainability decisions. Interns build direct relationships with operations, corporate leaders, and external partners, gaining a clear view of how environmental engineering supports business goals and community expectations. The experience emphasizes mentorship, data driven problem solving, and visible outcomes, creating a faster learning curve and a stronger professional network than many classroom style or observational internships.

 

Internship Location

This internship is located at Omni Corporate located in Fort Wayne, IN. This internship will take place in Summer 2026. For students who are local to Northeast Indiana area through the Spring 2026 school semester, this internship may be conducted part-time through the school year and transition into a Summer 2026 internship.

Internship Benefits

  • Furnished Housing Free of Cost
    • Provided for interns living more than 50 miles from their work site, including essential furnishings to ensure a comfortable stay during the internship.
  • 401(k) & Company Match
    • Eligibility to participate in the company 401(k) plan with a 10–50% company match that vests immediately.
  • Employee Discounts
    • Access to discounts on hotels, vehicles, and other goods and services through Steel Dynamics’ nationwide partner network.
  • Employee Assistance Program
    • Up to five free visits per issue, per year for counseling, legal advice, financial guidance, and other daily living resources.
  • Intern Extravaganza
    • A two-day event at company headquarters featuring facility tours, networking with company leaders, cultural immersion, and connecting with other interns from across the country.
  • Competitive Pay
    • Competitive hourly wages for all internship positions, rewarding the value interns bring to the company.

Responsibilities

What Are My Responsibilities as an Environmental Engineering Intern at Omni?

  • Support the ISO 14001 Environmental Management System by maintaining procedures, records, and continuous improvement actions across air, water, stormwater, waste, hazardous waste, spill prevention, and radiation programs.
  • Assist with environmental permitting by gathering data, drafting submittals, coordinating with consultants, and communicating with regulatory agencies.
  • Collect, validate, and analyze environmental data for emissions, water quality, and waste streams, and build tracking tools and reports to demonstrate compliance with permit limits.
  • Conduct field inspections of emission points, stormwater controls, waste accumulation areas, and radiation detection portals, document findings, and follow up on corrective actions.
  • Perform sampling and monitoring to verify compliance with permit conditions, maintain chain of custody, and organize sampling records.
  • Prepare or assist with required regulatory reports including emission inventories, Title V reports, SARA and Tier II submissions, deviation logs, discharge monitoring reports, and routine quarterly and annual filings.
  • Participate in root cause analyses for exceedances or abnormal trends and help develop corrective and preventive actions with operations and maintenance teams.
  • Support operation and performance tracking of pollution control equipment such as baghouses, scrubbers, and oxidizers, and recommend improvements where appropriate.
  • Contribute to sustainability and decarbonization initiatives focused on emissions reduction, waste minimization, water stewardship, and recycling.
  • Assist with contractor and vendor coordination, waste profiling and manifests, and value driven procurement to meet program goals.
  • Help prepare for audits and inspections by organizing documentation, participating in walk throughs, and supporting responses to findings or Notices of Violation.
  • Develop and deliver basic training or job aids for environmental requirements, and partner with the SDI Corporate Office on projects as needed.

Qualifications

What Qualifications Do I Need?

  • Pursuing a bachelor’s degree in Environmental Science, Environmental Policy, Environmental Engineering, or any science-related majors (Chemical, Biology, Ecology, etc.)
  • Clear communication and organized documentation skills to collaborate with operations and support compliance reporting
  • Minimum of 2.7 GPA

 

Steel Dynamics, Inc., and all affiliated entities are equal opportunity employers.
